<h1>grigson</h1>
<p>A plain-text format and toolkit for writing chord charts.
Source files use the <code>.chart</code> extension and look like the charts they describe —
pipe characters for bar lines, standard chord names, YAML front matter for metadata.</p>

<div class="hero-example">
  <div>
    <h3>Source</h3>
    {% highlight "grigson" %}---
title: Blues in F
key: F
---

[Head]
||: (4/4) F7 | % | % | % |
| Bb7 | % | F7 | % |
| C7 | Bb7 | F7 | C7 :||{% endhighlight %}
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Rendered</h3>
    <grigson-chart normalise>
      <template>---
title: Blues in F
key: F
---

[Head]
||: (4/4) F7 | % | % | % |
| Bb7 | % | F7 | % |
| C7 | Bb7 | F7 | C7 :||</template>
    </grigson-chart>
  </div>
</div>

